PFUAggDatabase 0.0.0.9000
  • Reference

    Create a targets workflow

    get_pipeline.Rd

    Arguments to this function specify the details of a targets workflow to be executed.

    get_pipeline(
  countries = NULL,
  psut_release,
  psut_releases_folder,
  exemplar_table_path,
  world_agg_map
)

    Arguments

    countries

    A string vector of 3-letter country codes. Default is NULL, meaning all countries should be analyzed.

    psut_release

    The release we'll use from psut_releases_folder.

    psut_releases_folder

    The path to the pins archive of PSUT releases.

    exemplar_table_path

    The path to the examplar table.

    world_agg_map

    The aggregation map to aggregate from continents to the world.

    Value

    A list of tar_targets to be executed in a workflow.

    Details

    The exemplar table is assumed to be an Excel file with the following columns: "Region.code" and years (as numbers). The body of the table should contain 3-letter codes of countries. The exemplar table is assumed to be on the "exemplar_table" tab of the Excel file.
